# fire-and-forget.allowlist — intentional `void asyncCall(...)`
# patterns that are deliberately fire-and-forget and either chain
# their own .catch OR are in a path where failure is definitively
# non-critical (e.g. observability hooks that can't themselves
# block shutdown).
#
# Every entry MUST carry a `# reason` comment on the line above
# OR inline. Adding entries without a reason fails review.
#
# Entry form:
#   path/to/file.ts:LINE:calleeName     (exact match)
#   path/to/file.ts:calleeName          (any-line match — use when
#                                        line numbers shift often)
#
# The guard is scripts/guards/check-no-fire-and-forget.ts
# and runs in CI. See CLAUDE.md §9.6 for the rationale.

# ── Observability / shutdown hooks ───────────────────────────────

# OpenTelemetry SIGTERM shutdown — calling shutdownOtel from a
# signal handler genuinely can't `await` (the process is about to
# exit) and any error is unrecoverable. Intentional fire-and-forget.
apps/api/src/observability/otel.ts:shutdownOtel

# ── Cron scheduler ticks (cron.schedule requires a sync callback) ──

# BullMQ / node-cron schedulers take a sync callback; wrapping an
# async tick() in `() => { void tick(); }` is the standard pattern.
# Each tick() has its own try/catch internally so unhandled
# rejections are impossible. Audit 2026-04-16 verified.
apps/api/src/jobs/schedulers/audioRetentionScheduler.ts:tick
apps/api/src/jobs/schedulers/matviewRefreshScheduler.ts:tick
apps/api/src/jobs/schedulers/backupScheduler.ts:tick
# HL7 ORM-O01 builder is fire-and-forget inside a BullMQ job
# handler — the outer worker catches everything and retries.
apps/api/src/jobs/workers/hl7Worker.ts:buildOrmO01
